1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,080
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:04,080 --> 00:00:05,080
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:05,080 --> 00:00:09,080
My name is Catherine and today we're talking about a very important topic.
我是Catherine，今天我们讨论一个非常重要的话题。

4
00:00:09,080 --> 00:00:10,960
This is about time.
这跟时间有关。

5
00:00:10,960 --> 00:00:11,960
That's right.
没错。

6
00:00:11,960 --> 00:00:17,120
So sometimes we are a little bit lazy or maybe we sleep too much and we're late to work or
所以有时候我们有点懒，或者睡太多，上班迟到，

7
00:00:17,120 --> 00:00:18,120
a meeting.
或者开会迟到。

8
00:00:18,120 --> 00:00:19,120
All right.
好的。

9
00:00:19,120 --> 00:00:21,420
So learn many different ways to talk about being late today.
所以今天学习多种谈论迟到的表达方式。

10
00:00:21,420 --> 00:00:24,240
Let's take a listen to our dialogue.
我们来听一下对话。

11
00:00:24,240 --> 00:00:27,000
Okay, everyone.
好了，各位。

12
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:29,960
Shall we begin?
我们可以开始了吗？

13
00:00:29,960 --> 00:00:32,320
Sorry Maggie, but we're missing a few people.
抱歉Maggie，我们还有几个人没到。

14
00:00:32,320 --> 00:00:33,320
Can we hang on a sec?
能稍等一下吗？

15
00:00:33,320 --> 00:00:37,760
Well, I did say 11 o'clock sharp and it's now five past.
嗯，我确实说了11点整，现在已经过了五分钟了。

16
00:00:37,760 --> 00:00:38,760
So...
所以……

17
00:00:38,760 --> 00:00:39,900
Hi, everyone.
大家好。

18
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:41,520
I'm so sorry I'm late.
非常抱歉我迟到了。

19
00:00:41,520 --> 00:00:45,840
It's raining cats and dogs outside and I had to wait ages for a taxi.
外面下着倾盆大雨，我等出租车等了很久。

20
00:00:45,840 --> 00:00:46,840
Okay, James.
好的，James。

21
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:48,640
Take a seat quickly, please.
请快点坐下。

22
00:00:48,640 --> 00:00:49,640
Right.
好的。

23
00:00:49,640 --> 00:00:51,320
The subject of the meeting is the importance.
会议的主题是重要性。

24
00:00:51,320 --> 00:00:52,560
Hi, guys.
嗨，大家好。

25
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:54,080
Please excuse me.
请原谅我。

26
00:00:54,080 --> 00:00:56,240
I was held up in traffic.
我被堵在路上了。

27
00:00:56,240 --> 00:00:57,400
Right.
好的。

28
00:00:57,400 --> 00:01:00,000
As I was saying, the subject of the meeting is...
正如我刚才所说，会议的主题是……

29
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:01,000
Hi, Maggie.
嗨，Maggie。

30
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:02,000
I'm terribly sorry.
我非常抱歉。

31
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:03,560
The traffic is murder out there.
外面交通简直糟透了。

32
00:01:03,560 --> 00:01:05,560
Sit down, Bruno.
坐下吧，Bruno。

33
00:01:05,560 --> 00:01:06,560
Okay.
好的。

34
00:01:06,560 --> 00:01:12,600
Now, as you're aware, the topic for the meeting is the importance of being punctual.
现在，正如你们所知，会议的主题是守时的重要性。

35
00:01:12,600 --> 00:01:14,160
Who would like to start?
谁想先发言？

36
00:01:14,160 --> 00:01:15,680
All right.
好的。

37
00:01:15,680 --> 00:01:17,280
We're back.
我们回来了。

38
00:01:17,280 --> 00:01:23,080
So now let's take a look at some of this vocab on Language Takeaway.
现在让我们看看“语言小贴士”中的一些词汇。

39
00:01:23,080 --> 00:01:25,460
Language Takeaway.
语言小贴士。

40
00:01:25,460 --> 00:01:28,000
So first up, we have a word that we heard.
首先，我们听到一个词。

41
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:31,400
The phrase was, I did say 11 o'clock sharp.
短语是：我确实说了11点整。

42
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:32,400
Okay.
好的。

43
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:36,840
So if you say the time, like 11 o'clock, and then you add sharp at the end, what does that
所以如果你说时间，比如11点，然后在后面加上sharp，

44
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:37,840
mean?
那是什么意思？

45
00:01:37,840 --> 00:01:38,840
That means exactly.
意思是“正好”。

46
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:42,840
So, 11 o'clock, exactly 11 o'clock.
所以，11点整，正好11点。

47
00:01:42,840 --> 00:01:44,580
11, zero, zero.
11点零分零秒。

48
00:01:44,580 --> 00:01:47,880
Not 1101, not 1102, but 11 o'clock.
不是11点01分，也不是11点02分，而是11点整。

49
00:01:47,880 --> 00:01:52,640
So if I say, I'll be there at three o'clock sharp.
所以如果我说：我会在三点整到。

50
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:55,360
That means you won't be there at 2.58.
意思是你不会在2点58分到。

51
00:01:55,360 --> 00:01:58,200
You will not be there at 3.04.
你也不会在3点04分到。

52
00:01:58,200 --> 00:01:59,820
You'll be there at three o'clock.
你会在三点整到。

53
00:01:59,820 --> 00:02:00,820
That's right.
没错。

54
00:02:00,820 --> 00:02:01,820
Okay.
好的。

55
00:02:01,820 --> 00:02:02,820
So three o'clock sharp.
所以三点整。

56
00:02:02,820 --> 00:02:06,960
So if you say the time and then you add sharp, it means at that exact time.
所以如果你说时间然后加上sharp，意思就是那个准确的时间。

57
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:08,880
Now James was late.
现在James迟到了。

58
00:02:08,880 --> 00:02:13,560
He said he was late because he had to wait ages for a taxi.
他说他迟到是因为等出租车等了很久。

59
00:02:13,560 --> 00:02:14,560
Okay.
好的。

60
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:18,600
So this might be confusing for some people, Marco, because I can say, what's your age?
这可能让一些人困惑，Marco，因为我可以问：你多大年纪？

61
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:20,320
How old are you?
你几岁？

62
00:02:20,320 --> 00:02:23,000
But here, ages has a different meaning.
但在这里，ages有不同的意思。

63
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:27,200
So I had to wait ages means I waited a very long time.
所以“我等了很久”意思是我等了很长时间。

64
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:28,200
That's right.
没错。

65
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:30,760
So the word ages means for a very long time.
所以单词ages意思是“很长时间”。

66
00:02:30,760 --> 00:02:32,920
It's always related to time in this sense.
在这个语境下，它总是和时间相关。

67
00:02:32,920 --> 00:02:33,920
Exactly.
正是。

68
00:02:33,920 --> 00:02:35,960
So I could say, Marco, it's so good to see you.
所以我可以这样说：Marco，见到你真好。

69
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:37,840
I haven't seen you in ages.
我好久没见到你了。

70
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:41,400
That means I haven't seen you in such a long time.
意思是我很久没见到你了。

71
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:42,400
Okay.
好的。

72
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:43,400
Very good.
很好。

73
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:49,040
And now the next person, Sally came in and she said she was held up in traffic.
现在下一个人，Sally进来了，她说她被堵在路上了。

74
00:02:49,040 --> 00:02:50,040
Okay.
好的。

75
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:54,680
So to be held up in traffic means to be stuck in traffic.
所以“被堵在路上”意思是“被困在交通中”。

76
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:59,960
That means you were made late because there were so many cars on the road.
意思是你因为路上车太多而迟到了。

77
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:00,960
Okay.
好的。

78
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:03,720
So somebody or something else made you late.
所以是某人或某事让你迟到了。

79
00:03:03,720 --> 00:03:04,720
That's right.
没错。

80
00:03:04,720 --> 00:03:06,560
So to be held up means to be made late.
所以“被耽搁”意思是“被弄迟了”。

81
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:09,820
I could ask you, Marco, why are you so late?
我可以问你，马可，你为什么这么晚？

82
00:03:09,820 --> 00:03:11,040
What held you up?
什么耽误了你？

83
00:03:11,040 --> 00:03:12,040
Exactly.
没错。

84
00:03:12,040 --> 00:03:13,040
What held you up?
什么耽误了你？

85
00:03:13,040 --> 00:03:15,280
That means what made me late.
意思是让我迟到的原因。

86
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:16,280
That's right.
对。

87
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:17,280
It could be many different things.
可能有很多不同的原因。

88
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:18,280
Okay.
好的。

89
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:19,280
Yeah.
嗯。

90
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:24,000
It could be traffic or maybe I could be held up by the doctor.
可能是交通，或者我可能被医生耽误了。

91
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:26,920
Maybe he took longer than what I expected.
也许他花的时间比我预期的长。

92
00:03:26,920 --> 00:03:31,400
Or there's no elevator and I'm waiting for the elevator and I got held up by the elevator.
或者没有电梯，我在等电梯，结果被电梯耽误了。

93
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,400
Okay.
好的。

94
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:33,400
Very good.
很好。

95
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:36,320
And now the importance of being punctual.
现在来说说准时的重要性。

96
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:37,920
That's the topic of the meeting.
这是会议的主题。

97
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:40,120
And so what is this word, punctual?
那么，这个词“准时”是什么意思？

98
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:41,120
Okay.
好的。

99
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:47,280
So punctual is an adjective and it describes something as being on time.
“准时”是一个形容词，用来描述某事是准时的。

100
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:48,280
Okay.
好的。

101
00:03:48,280 --> 00:03:50,520
So the opposite of this word would be what?
那么这个词的反义词是什么？

102
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:52,160
So the opposite would be late.
反义词是“迟到”。

103
00:03:52,160 --> 00:03:53,160
Late.
迟到。

104
00:03:53,160 --> 00:03:54,160
Okay.
好的。

105
00:03:54,160 --> 00:03:56,280
So she's a very punctual student.
她是一个非常准时的学生。

106
00:03:56,280 --> 00:03:59,200
She always comes to class on time.
她总是准时来上课。

107
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:00,520
She's never late.
她从不迟到。

108
00:04:00,520 --> 00:04:01,520
Punctual.
准时。

109
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:06,400
So you describe a person as being punctual or not.
所以你可以形容一个人是否准时。

110
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:07,400
That's right.
对。

111
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:08,400
Okay.
好的。

112
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:09,400
Very good.
很好。

113
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:10,400
Let's review all this vocab.
我们来复习一下这些词汇。

114
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:13,560
Let's go back and listen to the dialogue again.
我们回去再听一遍对话。

115
