The traffic is murder out there.
外面的交通简直要命。

135
00:04:52,680 --> 00:04:54,680
Sit down, Bruno.
坐下吧，布鲁诺。

136
00:04:54,680 --> 00:05:01,720
Okay, now, as you're aware, the topic for the meeting is the importance of being punctual.
好的，现在，正如你们所知，会议的主题是准时的重要性。

137
00:05:01,720 --> 00:05:03,720
Who would like to start?
谁想先发言？

138
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:06,000
All right.
好的。

139
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:10,480
Now let's take a look at some phrases on Fluency Builder.
现在让我们看看“流利度构建器”中的一些短语。

140
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:11,480
Fluency Builder.
流利度构建器。

141
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:15,560
We have a lot of really great phrases today that describe...
我们今天有很多很棒的短语，用来描述……

142
00:05:15,560 --> 00:05:20,920
Well, that are excuses for not being on time or for not being punctual.
嗯，就是那些为不准时或不守时找的借口。

143
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:23,440
The first one we heard was actually different, though.
不过，我们听到的第一个短语其实不一样。

144
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:26,600
One of the students said, can we hang on a sec?
其中一个学生说：“我们能稍等一下吗？”

145
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:28,040
Hang on a sec.
稍等一下。

146
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:29,040
Okay.
好的。

147
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:33,480
So, if you ask someone to hang on, that means to wait.
所以，如果你让别人“hang on”，意思是等待。

148
00:05:33,480 --> 00:05:34,480
Hang on.
等一下。

149
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:35,480
Wait.
等待。

150
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:36,480
Yeah, exactly.
嗯，没错。

151
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:37,480
So, hang on just means to wait.
所以，“hang on”就是等待的意思。

152
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:38,480
It's very casual.
这很随意。

153
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:39,480
Okay.
好的。

154
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:43,880
So, if you ask someone to hang on a sec, hang on a sec or hang on a minute, that means wait
所以，如果你让别人“hang on a sec”、“hang on a sec”或“hang on a minute”，意思是等

155
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:45,000
for a little while.
一小会儿。

156
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,000
A little while.
一小会儿。

157
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:49,560
A sec, S-E-C, stands for second.
“a sec”，S-E-C，代表“second”（秒）。

158
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:51,400
