这是很口语化的英语，尽管“sec”这个词并不真正存在。

165
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:06,040
It's just a short way of saying a second.
它只是“a second”的简短说法。

166
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:07,040
Exactly.
没错。

167
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:12,080
And later on, we heard James come in, he was one of those people that we had to wait for,
后来，我们听到詹姆斯进来了，他是我们不得不等的人之一，

168
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:15,880
and he said, it's raining cats and dogs outside.
他说，外面下着倾盆大雨。

169
00:06:15,880 --> 00:06:16,880
That's right.
对。

170
00:06:16,880 --> 00:06:17,880
Okay.
好的。

171
00:06:17,880 --> 00:06:18,880
It's raining cats and dogs.
下着倾盆大雨。

172
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:21,280
So, are cats and dogs falling from the sky?
所以，猫和狗真的从天上掉下来了吗？

173
00:06:21,280 --> 00:06:22,280
They are not.
不是的。

174
00:06:22,280 --> 00:06:24,540
So, this might sound very weird to you.
所以，这听起来可能很奇怪。

175
00:06:24,540 --> 00:06:29,360
This does not mean there are cats and dogs falling down from the clouds, but it does
这并不意味着有猫和狗从云上掉下来，而是

176
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:31,480
mean that it's raining a lot.
意味着雨下得很大。

177
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:33,520
It's raining really hard outside.
外面雨下得真大。

178
00:06:33,520 --> 00:06:34,880
Okay, very good.
好的，非常好。

179
00:06:34,880 --> 00:06:38,320
So, it's a phrase used to say it's raining a lot.
所以，这是一个用来表示雨下得很大的短语。

180
00:06:38,320 --> 00:06:40,480
It's raining very, very hard.
雨下得非常非常大。

181
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:41,480
Raining cats and dogs.
倾盆大雨。

182
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:45,560
So, Maggie is trying to continue with the meeting as many people keep coming in and
所以，玛吉试图继续开会，但很多人不断进来

183
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:46,560
disrupting her.
打断她。

184
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:51,800
So, she says, right, as I was saying, the subject of the meeting.
所以，她说，对，正如我刚才说的，会议的主题。

185
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:52,800
As I was saying.
正如我刚才说的。

